name: Plates - The Lolladoff Plate
description: The Lolladoff Plate is a 12,000-year-old stone dish depicting a hovering disk-shaped object and a small being resembling an alien gray.

name: Adoration of the Child with St. Benedict and Angels
description: Adoration of the Child with St. Benedict and Angels by Vincenzo Foppa.

name: Sun on Fresque Saint-Jean-Baptiste
description: Detail of Sun on Fresque du plafond de l’église Saint-Jean-Baptiste de Larbey.

name: Ancient Chinese Illustration
description: Old Chinese illustration from 'Illustrated Survey of Weird Countries' showing flying cars and alien-like vehicles.

name: Madonna with UFO
description: Fourteenth-century fresco depicting Madonna and Child with a UFO hovering above.

name: Baptism of Christ by Rogier van der Weyden
description: Baptism of Christ depicting UFOs or lenticular clouds.

name: Baptism of Christ by Ottavio Vannini
description: Baptism of Christ showing a UFO-like object.

name: Crucifixion Fresco - Visoki Decani Monestary
description: 1350 painting depicting a crucifixion scene with spaceships, featuring a man observing a flying vehicle decorated with twinkling stars. Located above the altar at Visoki Decani Monestary in Kosovo, Yugoslavia.

name: Ancient Aircraft in History
description: Ancient depictions of aircraft, possibly representing UFO-like objects.

name: Vimanas in Ancient India
description: Ancient Indian depictions of Vimanas, possibly representing advanced aircraft or extraterrestrial vehicles.

name: Golden UFO Illumination
description: Illumination of Fortuna in Le livre de bonnes meurs de Jacque Legrand by Jacque Legrand.

name: The Annunciation with Saint Emidius
description: The Annunciation with Saint Emidius by Carlo Crivelli, featuring vortex and dove details.

name: T-O Map
description: T-O Map in Etymologiae by Isidore, Bishop of Seville.
source: Library of Congress Rare Book and Special Collections Division

name: Madonna with Saint Giovannino
description: The Madonna with Saint Giovannino attributed to Domenico Ghirlandaio.

name: Tassili n'Ajjer Rock Art
description: Rock art from Tassili n'Ajjer, Sahara Desert, depicting herds, wild animals, and possibly spacemen.

name: Wandjina Petroglyphs
description: Wandjina petroglyphs from Kimberley, Australia, possibly representing alien beings.

name: Japanese Labyrinth Relief
description: Artistic reproductions of reliefs depicting humans in astronaut-like suits and solar system illustrations.

name: Cave Paintings - Tanzania
description: Two cave paintings from Tanzania depicting disc-shaped objects and entities surrounding a woman, estimated up to 29,000 years old.

name: Dutch Ships UFO Sighting
description: Illustration depicting a UFO sighting by two Dutch ships in the North Sea, 1680.
source: Theatrum Orbis Terrarum by Admiral Blaeu

name: Crucifixion with UFOs
description: Multiple frescoes and paintings depicting crucifixion scenes with saucer-shaped crafts and UFO-like objects.

name: UFO's in Religious Art
description: Painting depicting Moses receiving the Ten Commandments with flaming UFO-like objects in the sky.

name: Baptism of Christ - De Gelder
description: Painted by Aert de Gelder circa 1710, this artwork depicts the baptism of Jesus by John the Baptist at the River Jordan. A large disc in the sky emits beams of light, interpreted by some as a UFO, while traditionally seen as the Spirit of God descending like a dove.

name: Glorification of the Eucharist
description: Painting 'Glorification of the Eucharist' by Bonaventura Salimbeni (1600), depicting Jesus and a 'Sputnik satellite-like device' in the church of San Lorenzo in San Pietro, Montalcino, Italy.
source: San Lorenzo in San Pietro, Montalcino

name: Crucifixion Painting - Svetishoveli Cathedral
description: 17th century fresco of the crucifixion at Svetishoveli Cathedral in Mtskheta, Georgia, featuring two saucer-shaped crafts on either side of Christ.

name: The Magnificent - Notre-Dame in Beaune
description: 'The Magnificent' tapestry from 1330, located at Notre-Dame in Beaune, Burgundy.

name: The Miracle of the Snow
description: Painting 'The Miracle of the Snow' by Masolino Da Panicale (1383-1440), depicting Jesus and Mary with UFOs or lenticular clouds, housed at the church of San Lorenzo in San Pietro, Montalcino, Italy.
source: San Lorenzo in San Pietro, Montalcino

name: Lenticular Clouds or UFOs?
description: Painting 'Lenticular Clouds or UFOs?' painted in 1420, located at San Francesco Church in Arezzo, Italy, depicting Jesus and Mary with UFO-like objects or lenticular clouds.

name: Woodcut - Rocket Ship Arabia
description: Woodcuts from Arabia (1479) and Nurnberg Germany (1561) depicting rocket ships and battles between aliens.

name: Madonna Adoring the Christ Child
description: Tempera panel showing a circular opening in the sky with three figures.

name: Cave Painting - Val Camonica
description: Cave painting depicting aliens creating a human fetus, dated c.10,000 BC from Val Camonica, Italy.

name: Miracle of the Snow
description: Painting depicting Jesus and Mary with UFOs or lenticular clouds, titled 'The Miracle of the Snow'.
source: San Lorenzo in San Pietro, Montalcino

name: Baptism of Christ - Aert De Gelder
description: Disk-shaped object shining beams of light on John the Baptist and Jesus, painted by Aert De Gelder.

name: Baptism of Christ by Fra Angelico
description: Baptism of Christ with a UFO hovering above.

name: Madonna with Saint Giovannino - Mother Mary
description: Fourteenth-century fresco 'The Madonna with Saint Giovannino' by Domenico Ghirlandaio, depicting Madonna and Child with a UFO hovering above, located in the Loeser collection, Palazzo Vecchio.

name: La Tebaide
description: Crucifixion painting by Paolo Uccello, circa 1460-1465.

name: UFO Coin
description: A French coin minted in 1680 showing a hovering disc-shaped UFO with portholes or lights around the rim.
